2. Consider the charging time: while some electric cars can charge quickly, others may take several hours to fully charge. Be aware of the charging time and plan your day accordingly.
3. Test the car's features: electric cars often come equipped with advanced features such as regenerative braking, adaptive cruise control, and automatic emergency braking.
